RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: Saints or Sinners and Seahawk Racing

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PENS STREET stalked two then three wide, drew alongside the top pair from outside on the backstretch, vied for the lead through the far turn, cleared leaving the bend, drew off when roused and was ridden out to the wire. BANDEENA broke a hair slow, chased two then three wide around the clubhouse turn, challenged four deep on the second bend, was no match for the winner in the lane but was clearly second best. A BROKEN BREEZE rated along the inside for a bit before going up to duel for command into the backstretch, fought into and around the far turn, could not kick on with the winner at the top of the lane and weakened. THE REIGN SONG broke out then got hustled to the front, crossed over once clear of inner rival, dueled outside A BROKEN BREEZE into the backstretch, vied between rivals around the far turn, failed to keep up into the lane and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: The Reign Song
ENTRY.OWNER: Halasz Thomas E and Lovingier Terry C
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, cleared, dueled outside, between, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 92. Claiming Purse 30000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRIMSON ROSE was closest in pursuit to the outside of the leader into the turn, drew alongside at the three-eighths pole, floated out by BENGAL TIGER leaving the bend, kicked clear in upper stretch and widened through the lane while kept to task. SUGAR SUGAR chased three deep into the turn, came four wide into the lane, moved out in upper stretch and bested the rest. LASTING LOVE chased along the rail, steered out in upper stretch and was denied second. TIP TOP GAL broke a step slow and was crowded a bit shortly after, ran up on heels approaching the nine-sixteenths pole, chased between foes into the turn, ran two wide through the turn and passed tired rivals. KEYCHAIN GIRL stalked the pace from inside, cut the corner into the lane, asked in upper stretch and failed to respond. BENGAL TIGER away quickly to take control, challenged from outside at the three-eighths pole, drifted into the lane and weakened once overtaken.

ENTRY.NAME: Lasting Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, moved out upper, denied 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Tip Top Gal
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, on heels early, 2wide, passed tired rivals

ENTRY.NAME: Crimson Rose
ENTRY.OWNER: A and J Racing and Flight 4 Partners
ENTRY.COMMENT: closest, bid outside 3/8, floated into str, cleared, widened

ENTRY.NAME: Bengal Tiger
ENTRY.OWNER: Farias Adan Newman Robert Schadick David and Sylvia Earle
ENTRY.COMMENT: away quickly, challenge 3/8, drifted into str, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Sugar Sugar
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 3deep, 4wide into str, moved out, bested rest

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 97. Claiming Purse 30000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PATRON D'ORO dueled outside OIL CAN KNIGHT to the turn, cleared with three furlongs left to run and was kept to task through the lane. OIL CAN KNIGHT dueled for the lead from inside, lost touch with the winner at the three-eighths pole, chased two wide into the drive, churned on through the lane and proved second best. MOLTO VIVACE forwardly placed three deep, chased four wide leaving the turn, could not summon the needed rally but stayed on to secure the show. ESTABLISHED chased four deep up the backstretch, spun five wide into the lane and weakened. PACO'S PICO chased five deep into the turn, six wide into the stretch and weakened. ALPINE THUNDER trailed off the rail, raced two wide into the turn then moved inside, saved ground to the stretch and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Oil Can Knight
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC and Medina Lizbeth

ENTRY.NAME: Patron d'Oro
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled outside, cleared 3/8, kept to task

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 86. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EAGLES LANDING broke well then stalked the leading duo up the backstretch, chased two to three wide on the turn, was closest in pursuit entering the final furlong, drew alongside HABEAS with a sixteenth remaining and drove past. HABEAS set the pace under pressure from outer rival, put away that foe at the three-eighths pole, showed the way from off the rail into the drive, led clear into the final furlong, challenged by the winner at the sixteenth pole and yielded late. BARTON STRONG got crowded a bit early, chased two wide into the turn, went three to four wide into the lane, summoned a mild rally and was along for the show honors. SOUTH COAST ROUTE bumped leaving the gate, chased two then three wide around the turn, churned on for a minor award but failed to threaten. KING ZOG tracked the pace from inside and lacked a rally in the drive. CRYPTOHOLIC got bumped on both sides leaving the gate, climbed early and dropped back, steered out wide, went five then six wide on the turn and improved placings in the lane. REEF CITY settled inside, coaxed on the inside around the turn, angled out in the stretch and failed to menace. SEA BREEZE BOY broke in and bumped, pressed in hand from outside, lost touch with the leader at the three-eighths pole, came five wide into the lane, moved inward in upper stretch and weakened. MT. ZEROR sat off the pace, navigated the turn four wide and was not a factor. I GOT A GUY broke in and bumped, chased near the back off the inside, rounded the bend three wide and made no impact. NYQUILER got pinballed leaving the gate, chased four wide into the turn, five wide into the lane and faded. REAL THIRSTY bumped at the start, chased five wide into the turn, dropped back around the bend and had little left for the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Reef City
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside, angled out, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: King Zog
ENTRY.OWNER: Aldrich III Frank C Aldrich MarySue and Miyadi Steven

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, stalked duo, chased 2wide, overhauled foe

ENTRY.OWNER: Gem Inc and Pell Richard C

ENTRY.NAME: Cryptoholic
ENTRY.OWNER: Mark D and Patricia L Cofer Trust and Webb Family Trust
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped both sides start, climbed, 5-6wide, improved

ENTRY.NAME: Nyquiler
ENTRY.OWNER: Guernsey Jade H and Osborne Candice J

ENTRY.NAME: Sea Breeze Boy
ENTRY.OWNER: Conner Dennis Jacobsen Wade and McKeen Michael
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in/bumped, pressed in hand, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 90. Starter Allowance Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $6,250 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEWPARK (IRE) dueled inside a rival up the backstretch, drifted out and bumped into the turn, inched ahead midstretch and drove clear in the furlong grounds. PERFECT D stalked in the two path into the turn, angled out and came four wide into the lane, bid three deep midstretch and was turned away by the winner. WHISKY MY GOD (ARG) dueled for the lead from outside, bumped entering the turn, fought to the eighth pole and faltered in deep stretch. ELUSIVE VIRTUE broke a step slow, sat off the pace, angled out around the bend and came four wide into the stretch and never threatened. HIGH PRESS bobbled leaving the gate, stalked three deep then angled leaving the backstretch, saved ground through the turn, steered out in the lane and weakened. AFTERNOON HEAT sat off the pace, saved ground along the rail through the turn and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Afternoon Heat
ENTRY.OWNER: Delgado Nicholas Pober Lloyd and Treece Charles S

ENTRY.NAME: Elusive Virtue
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, off pace, 2-4wide, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: High Press
ENTRY.OWNER: Sides Clay R and Valenzuela Jr Martin
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled, stalked 3deep, angled in, moved out str, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 93. Starter Allowance Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $25,000 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HENNYS CRAZY TRAIN chased along the inside into the first turn then angled out to the three path around the bend, coaxed along two then three wide on the far turn, steered out into the stretch, moved outside the drifting leader with a furlong left to run and edged away. SHE'S A BIT SASSY sped to the front in the two path, showed the way under pressure to the second bend, was overtaken past the seven-sixteenths pole, chased the new leader into the lane, came back on in the furlong grounds and gained the place. SIGNORA MINISTER chased four wide around the first turn, went up to press from outside on the backstretch, took over early on the far turn then cleared at the three-eighths pole, drifted out to the five path on that bend, drifted out further in the lane while maintaining a short lead into the final furlong and yielded in deep stretch. INDY'S STAR chased five then four wide around the clubhouse turn, went three wide into the second bend, spun five wide into the drive and weakened. WHISTLER'S STYLE broke a bit slow and lost his path at the start, trailed three wide early on, four wide into the far turn, six wide into the stretch and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Signora Minister
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, 4wide, pressed, cleared 3/8, drifted out, yielded

ENTRY.NAME: Whistler's Style
ENTRY.OWNER: Cohen Stuart Fritts Marie J Pellman Harry and Seymour Lauri
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost path start, trailed 3wide, 4-6wide, no factor

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRUSTY RUSTY stalked the top pair from outside, bid three deep on the turn, took over in upper stretch, maintained a short advantage over PAPA TIGER through the final furlong and gamely prevailed. PAPA TIGER dueled for command outside a rival, inched ahead from inner foe around the bend but had to contend with TRUSTY RUSTY challenging also from outside, lost command in upper stretch, fought back from inside through the final furlong and proved a game second. ALL THE KING'S MEN dueled for the lead from inside, lost touch with the top pair late on the turn, moved out in the lane continuing to give chase within striking distance, angled outside the leaders with a sixteenth to go and came back on for a game third. NEW YORK DREAMS (GB) sat off the pace, went two to three wide around the bend, steered inward in the drive and finished with a mild rally. GOLF DRAMA became antsy in the gate and had his head turned as the gates opened then got bumped, raced near the back three wide into the turn, angled out and came six wide into the stretch and finished with a mild rally. CATHEDRAL LIGHT stalked from inside, moved out in the stretch and finished evenly. IMPERIAL HORNET broke in and bumped rival, sat off the pace four to five wide on the turn and weakened. MENTIROSA traveled near the back well off the rail, went five wide into the turn, seven wide into the stretch and failed to menace. WARRENS WORLD chased in the two path leaving the backstretch, entered the stretch four wide and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: All the King's Men
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled inside, chased, angled out, came back

ENTRY.NAME: Warrens World
ENTRY.OWNER: Warren Benjamin C and Warren Sally

ENTRY.NAME: Golf Drama
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Edward Rusty J and Stanton Mark

ENTRY.NAME: Imperial Hornet
ENTRY.OWNER: Shapiro Thomas A and Shapiro Deborah

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 98. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 52000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winner s Of A Race Since June 23 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GYPSY TEARS stalked the leaders to the turn, bid three deep around the bend, kicked clear and drew away midstretch, ridden along to the sixteenth pole then held safely in hand late. RIFEY was off a bit slow from outside, trailed up the backstretch, saved ground through the turn, steered out in the lane, came with a late run but was too late. SAULS CALL dueled outside a rival, fought two wide through the turn, lost command into the stretch, could not go on with the winner in upper stretch and angled out, then weakened to third. SO I'M TOLD dueled inside SAULS CALL, lost touch with outer pair leaving the bend and weakened in the lane. NOLONGERAHOBBY sat off the pace, went four then five wide around the bend and failed to menace. RACHEL'S COACH stumbled badly, chased three wide into the turn, moved out and exited the bend five wide and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Gypsy Tears
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, bid 3deep, cleared upper, drew away, in hand late

ENTRY.NAME: So I'm Told
ENTRY.OWNER: Mojarro Racing LLC and Carlos Felipe

ENTRY.NAME: Sauls Call
ENTRY.OWNER: KN Racing and Beach Joanie Orr

ENTRY.NAME: Rifey
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit slow, saved ground, angled out, late run

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Dark Mirage S. LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 1M Dirt CR: 97. Stakes Purse 125000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD . By Subscription of $50 each to accompany the nomination. Supplementary nomination of $250 due at time of entry, $250 additional to start, with $75,000 Guaranteed with $41,250 to the winner, $13,500 to S econd, $9,000 to Third, $4,500 to Fourth, $3,000 to Fifth, $1,500 to Sixth, $750 to Seventh and Eighth and $375 to Ninth and Tenth. Three year olds 121 lbs. Older 124 lbs. Non winners of a race other than claiming at one mile or over allowed 3 lbs. One M ile. Nominations closed Thursday, September 14, 2023 with 17. (If there are less than six (6) Starters, the purse will be reduced to $75,000).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: YUKI (CHI) sped clear and moved into the two path, showed the way up the backstretch, drifted out late on the far turn, continued to drift out through the stretch, remained clear into the final sixteenth and held well over the late charge from the runner-up. SMOOTHLIKEBUTTAH tossed her head at the start, settled at the back, trailed three wide into the far turn, moved in a bit then swung out late on the bend, steered out wider in upper stretch, came with a late rush but was not enough. TROUVILLE tracked in the two path, came three wide into the stretch, split foes at the three-sixteenths pole, finished willingly in deep stretch but lost the place. GANADORA stumbled in the beginning, chased three deep around the clubhouse turn, was closest in pursuit into the far turn, entered the lane five wide, churned on through the lane and missed the show honors. ANGEL NADESHIKO stalked along the inside, asked two wide leaving the far turn and lacked a bid in the furlong grounds. GILA rated between rivals early, chased in the two path leaving the backstretch, exited the far turn four wide, moved out and flattened in the late stages. CHISMOSA broke out slightly, pulled three to four wide early, was a bit rank early on the backstretch, raced within striking distance four wide into the second bend, spun six wide into the stretch and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Gila
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated between, chased 2-4wide, moved out, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Smoothlikebuttah
ENTRY.OWNER: Bach Robert A and Tessar William
ENTRY.COMMENT: tossed head/off slow, inside-2wide, 3-2wide, angled out,late rush
